Right. It is.
The Processor generates same position for all position-less registrations, which fails commit-validationtest.

Surprisingly this Lambda caused the test to fail on CNFE when instantiating the Iterator (test checks if the instanceCreate works), as nbjavac's *Element were not available at test time. Moving to a subclass delayed linkage (the task actually never runs during test)
Fine.

The problem is that with MIME being hierarchical, a single position defined in text/x-java means, that if anyone registers a general service (in /):

if position is not specified, that service faisl commit-validation as the sequence text/x-java/* + /* contains both defined and undefined positions
if general service does define position, then all MIMEs other than java must start to provide positions.

So as discussed with @JaroslavTulach, it's far more safer to generate some positions always.
The goal is to:

generate position
prefer more specific (lower in the folder hierarchy) registrations
define some stable order
generate different numbers :-)

Note the exclusion of the "" (none) subfolder: various services are registered in Editors/ (or relevant MIME) directly which do NOT have position at the moment, and are registerd manually (entries in layers.xml, ...). Tons of changes would happen if positions would be generated by the annotation processor there. So this change only affect "named" service subfolders.
Right, generate some positions always.
Turned out to be a problem when commit-validation was run on clustrer.config=platform (no keymaps there)
Couldn't, by a chance, the check for Projects/.+/Lookup be removed by using the same trick with autogenerating the position? No need to solve it in this PR however.

Maybe I could save the API change entirely by removing the extra (not effectively used) registration completely, leaving the registration on PayaraDescriptorDataLoader only.
